The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Calcutta, Feb. 9: The Chatterjee Group (TCG)is ready to co-habit with Indian Oil (IOC) if it remained as a portfolio investor in Haldia Petrochemicals (HPL). Sources said since the Company Law Board order had upheld the allotment of 150 million shares to IOC, TCG was willing to work together with IOC if it remained only as a portfolio investor in HPL.

 Mumbai, Feb. 9: Indias forex reserves increased by $995 million to $180.047 billion in the week ended February 2 against $179.052 billion in the previous week. The reserves were up by $924 million a week ago.

 New Delhi, Feb. 9: In a relief to telecom operators facing penalty for non-fulfilment of roll out obligations, the government has deferred a decision as the Telecom Engineering Consultant could not provide the details. The telecom commission has decided that the issue would be looked into afresh.

 New Delhi, Feb. 9: The government today gave its nod to NTPC Ltd to enter into nuclear power generation. A company official said they would announce their plans by the end of 2007-08.




